quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,11,"Say, \"I am indeed commanded to worship Allah, consecrating my lifestyle exclusively to Him"
  39,12,And I am commanded to be the first of those who surrender to Him
  39,13,"Say, \"I do indeed fear the punishment of a dreadful Day if I disobey my Lord"
  39,14,"Say, \"Allah shall I worship, consecrating my lifestyle exclusively to Him"
  39,15,"You worship whomsoever you please, then, apart from Him.\" Say, \"Those, indeed, shall be the losers who will have lost their own selves and their kith and kin on the Day of Resurrection! Is that not obviously the real loss"
  39,16,"For them, sheets of fire above them and sheets beneath them! This is what Allah warns His subjects against. \"Fear me then, O you subjects of Mine"
  39,17,And those who eschew worshipping false gods and return penitently to Allah — good news for them! (O Prophet!) Give good news to My subjects
  39,18,"Those who pay heed to the Word [Qur'aan] and follow the the good guidance thereof. Those are the ones whom Allah has guided. And those are the ones endowed with insight"
  39,19,What about the one on whom the sentence of punishment is decreed — can you save the one already in the Fire
  39,20,But for those who fear their Lord there shall be chambers built over chambers beneath which rivers flow. Allahճ promise — and never does Allah fail to fulfill His promise
  39,21,"Do you not see that Allah sent down water from the sky, then made it flow on earth as resources of water, and then with it He brings out vegetation of various hues. Then this vegetation withers, and you see it turn yellow, and then He reduces it to rubble? Indeed there is a lesson in this for those endowed with insight"